By Ahmed Ubandoma Abuja – The Independent Hajj Reporters a Non Governmental Organisation(NGO), has commiserated with the Government and People of Saudi Arabia over the death of the country’s Ambassador to Nigeria Adnan Bostaji. The National Coordinator of the group Mr Ibrahim Muhammad, disclosed this on Thursday in a statement in Abuja. Muhammad expressed shock over the sudden death of the Ambassador. According to him, the deceased died in his sleep less than 20 hours after his return from Saudi Arabia. ”We are inspired by late Bostaji’s uncommon humility and in the course of his shared responsibilities towards reporting Hajj/Umrah activities and in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. ” We prayed Almighty Allah to grant his soul Al Janna Firdausi,” he said. (NAN)